    {
      "id": "s1-5",
      "sectionId": "s1",
      "title": "Crontab command",
      "body": "| -            | -                                                                       |\n| ------------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| `crontab -e` | Edit or create a crontab file if doesn’t already exist.                 |\n| `crontab -l` | Display the crontab file.                                               |\n| `crontab -r` | Remove the crontab file.                                                |\n| `crontab -v` | Display the last time you edited your crontab file.\\n_(non-standard)_ |"
